descript.abstract:
DESCRIPTION: Chapters is a map of the Navajo Nations 110 local political units called Chapters. These boundaries are used for political and administrative purpose, although they were originally created as, 'Land Management Units' in the 1930's by the BIA. (Ref GD-1937)
SOURCE: BIA, ONLA, US Census, Water Management staff, 1:100,000 scale.
DATA-ITEMS:
CHAPTER: 4 letter unique Chapter code. Every polygon that belongs to a Chapter has a code. Some Chapters have more than one polygon.
CMMTY: The actual full name of the Chapter. For Chapters with more than one polygon, only one of the polygons has a value.
GD: Grazing district number. Every polygon that belongs to a Chapter has a district number.
AGENCY: 6 letter BIA Agency code. Every polygon that belongs to a Chapter has an Agency code.
NAVNAME: Navajo name for Chapter.
CEN-80: American Indian resident population for 1980. From table CH06, 'Population and housing characteristics of the Navajo Nation, 1993, Division of Community Development, Navajo Nation.
CEN-90: American Indian resident population for 1990. Source same as CEN-80.
IHS-POP: Chapter population figures from Indian Health Service for fiscal year 1986. No documentation available.
IHS-UNIT: Indian Health Service, Administrative Service unit name.
RGV82: Number of registered voters in Chapter in 1982.
COMMENT: Status notes for polygons that don't belong to a CHAPTER.
USAGE: To select just one record for every Chapter use 'Reselect Chapters poly CMMTY> ' '. This produces 110 records that have a full set of data such as POP figures.
COMMENTS: The user should be aware that various versions of Chapter boundary maps exist within the Navajo Tribe and that'Chapter Boundaries' are a nebulous and sometimes volatile subject related to politics, grazing disputes, elections and general lack of coherent land use policies. The set of boundaries on this map does not exactly correspond to census tracts. Population figures should not be used in density calculations rather as point or label attributes. Since boundaries do not 'officially' exist for Cove, Newcomb, Cudeii, Shiprock, Hogback and San Juan Chapters, these boundaries have been assumed for the purpose of having a polygon. This map layer should not be considered a legal boundary document.
HISTORY: Grazing district boundaries for trust portions were delineated by Gallup BIA Soils office. All other district and Chapter boundaries were delineated by ONLA. All work was done on mylar and digitized at 1:100,000 scale. 09/21/94
